Ancient grains, succulent sweetcorn and aromatic beef are topped with fresh lime juice
and fragrant coriander in this mouth-watering, simple and satisfying meal inspired by
some of the most delicious flavours of South America.

== Quinoa ==

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the @quinoa{170%grams}.

Stir in the quinoa and bring back to the boil.

Cook until the quinoa has doubled in size and the seed has visibly split, ~{12-15%mins}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and return to the pot, off the heat.

Cover with a #lid{} and set aside.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

== Beef Mince ==

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1%unit} and discard the core and seeds. Slice
into thin strips.

Place a large pan over medium-high heat (without oil).

Once hot, fry the @Irish beef mince{250%grams} and sliced pepper until browned,
~{5-6%mins}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the beef as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked
> when no longer pink in the middle.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add the @ground cumin{1%sachet}, @ground coriander{1%sachet} and half the
@ground cinnamon{1/2%sachet} to the mince.

Mix together and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

Stir in the @chopped tomato with onion & garlic{1%pack}, ¼ tsp salt and ½ tsp
@?sugar{to taste}.

Bring to the boil, cover and simmer for ~{8-10%mins}.

== Quinoa and Corn ==

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{1%pack} in a sieve.

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%grams}(fresh) (stalks and all).

Quarter the @lime{1%unit}.

Mix the drained quinoa with the corn, @paprika{1%sachet} and juice from half
the lime wedges.

Season well with salt and pepper.

== Finishing ==

Once the fragrant beef mince is ready, remove the pan from the heat.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{65%grams} and allow to warm through, ~{1-2%mins}.

Add a splash of @?water{to taste} to loosen if required.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide the mince between plates.

Serve the quinoa and corn alongside.

Garnish with fresh coriander.